.nh
.TH "PGMCTL" "1" "May 2026" "pgman-proxy" "pgmctl Manual"

.SH NAME
pgmctl-explain - Compose a plain-English narrative from cluster facts


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpgmctl explain  [] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
pgmctl explain  renders a three-section narrative
(Diagnosis / Evidence / Suggested next steps) by composing the existing
data layers: GET /v1/status, GET /v1/diagnose, POST /v1/doctor/run, and
GET /v1/history.

.PP
Subjects (FR-018):
  failover-stuck                  Why isn't a recently-elected leader being
                                  recognised by the rest of the cluster?
  node-not-promoting        Why hasn't  been promoted yet?
  replication-broken        Why is  not streaming WAL?
  leader-election                 Recent leader-election history.
  current-state                   One-line cluster shape rollup.
  last-event                      Most recent history record + its context.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0  narrative rendered
  4  EX_SUBJECT_NA — subject's premise doesn't match cluster state


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for explain


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--cluster\fP=""
	Expected cluster id; pinned before any cluster-affecting op

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	Path to pgmctl config (overrides $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pgmctl/config.yaml)

.PP
\fB--context\fP=""
	Configured context name

.PP
\fB--endpoint\fP=""
	Single-shot pgman-proxy endpoint override

.PP
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Skip cluster-name confirmation (requires --cluster )

.PP
\fB--insecure-skip-tls-verify\fP[=false]
	Disable TLS verification (warned)

.PP
\fB--insecure-skip-version-check\fP[=false]
	Proceed despite minor / major version skew

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Suppress ANSI escapes unconditionally

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format (table, json, yaml, wide)

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--strict\fP[=false]
	Treat WARN as non-zero exit

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=10s
	Overall command timeout

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=0]
	Increase verbosity (-v / -vv / -vvv)

.PP
\fB-y\fP, \fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip single-resource confirmation prompts


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBpgmctl(1)\fP
